{{emerge|www-apps/owncloud}}

If you have the vhosts USE flag enabled, than you can run:

{{RootCmd|webapp-config -I -h myDomain.com -d cloud owncloud 5.0.13-r1}}

to install the owncloud server version 5.0.13-r1 for the domain <code>myDomain.com</code> to the directory {{Path|cloud}} which is normally located in {{Path|/var/www/myDomain.com/htdocs/}}

* ENABLE APC
PHP_TARGETS="php5-4" emerge -av dev-php/pecl-apc

Then restart php-fpm
/etc/init.d/php-fpm restart

If you want check if apc is working, copy apc.php in your www
cp /usr/share/php/apc/apc.php /var/www/

and then open it with your preferred browser
* ENABLE MEMCACHED

=== Owncloud Client ===
USE="qt4"

  emerge dev-libs/iniparser dev-ruby/sqlite3 net-libs/neon app-doc/doxygen dev-qt/qttest
Optional cmocka

Then follow the guide: http://doc.owncloud.org/desktop/1.3/building.html

  mkdir owncloud-build
  cd owncloud-build
  git clone http://git.csync.org/users/freitag/csync.git ocsync
  git clone http://github.com/owncloud/mirall.git 

  mkdir ocsync-build
  mkdir mirall-build

  cd ocsync
  git checkout dav

  cd ../ocsync-build
  cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE="Debug" ../ocsync
  make
  sudo make install

  cd ../mirall-build
  cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE="Debug" ../mirall \
        -DCSYNC_BUILD_PATH=../ocsync-build \
        -DCSYNC_INCLUDE_PATH=../ocsync/src
  make
  sudo make install	  


